<item>
            <title>[LU-4525] Distinguish FID/object visibility for otable-based iteration by the iteration caller (LFSCK) instead of OSD</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4525</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the ldiskfs otable-based iteration only returns namespace visible objects. That means the OSD needs to distinguish the FID/object visibility. But the OSD should not has the knowledge about the FID/object visibility. It is the iteration caller&apos;s duty to distinguish that by itself.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
